== Romanian ==
=== Etymology ===
Earlier in the 20th century ''sută'' was commonly held to be an early loan from [[Old Slavonic]], and some Romanian etymological dictionaries still derive it thus. Linguists in recent decades however, due to considerations of phonetic evolution, are moving
toward a pre-Roman source for the Romanian word, rather than an Old Slavonic source. The [[W:Romanian Academy|Romanian Academy]] in its official etymological dictionary does not derive the word from Old Slavonic. In either case, the word ultimately derives from PIE *''kmtom-'', "hundred", by way of a [[satem]] language.
===Cardinal number===
'''sută''' {{f}}, pl. ''[[sute]]''
#(one) [[hundred]].
